			<div class="content" id="post-content-2472477">
									

<p>Right. What I feared from the start happened&#8230; ;&gt;</p>
<p>I know nothing, or next to nothing about GOI-formats in general, and AWCY? in particular. So there is no way for me to know that this is an AWCY? document, except the tag which is unfortunately at the bottom of the document, whilst I usually prefer reading documents from the top.</p>
<p>Useless to say that as a consequence, this contribution to the MTF contest entry never made much sense to me from start to finish. I thought this was a project (?) submitted to the Foundation. And for a while I thought that this was the origin of ETA-11 not having much work (as stated in <em>A Convincing Lyre</em>): because they're a bunch of failures&#8230;</p>
<p>Another nitpick is that while I did consult SCP-1237's article since it was openly mentioned in the text, I did not consult the other SCPs referred - because how am I supposed to know where to jump with 'Rush' and 'Zoe'????<br />
It would be quite nice to put some discreet but enlightening links in there!</p>
<p>I am going to novote on this one - I simply do not feel competent to vote any other way. Though, in view of the above&#8230; I should downvote, because my second nitpick is, I feel, justified outside of my lack of interest so far for GOI-formats.<br />
Let's say it's a <em>negative novote</em>. 8-P</p>

